The [method](https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/bb198903%28v=xnagamestudio.40%29.aspx) from XNA 4.0 is not yet implemented in MonoGame.
(instead there  is thecommented block:
`/*
        public void SetValue (int[] value)
        {
            throw new NotImplementedException();
        }
        */` )

This code works in Windows version:
 songs = new Dictionary<string, XSong>();
 for (int i = 0; i < soundManagerInit.songs.Count; i++)
 {
         XSong song = new XSong();
         song.InitXSong(soundManagerInit.songs[i]);
         song.Song = game.Content.Load<Song>(@"sounds\songs\" + song.FileName);
         songs.Add(soundManagerInit.songs[i].name, song);
  }
and song plays with
MediaPlayer.Play(songs["Battle March"].Song);
but in Windows GL the Load gives the following error:
 Specified stream is not a wave file.
the only difference is a reference to the appropriate version.

Is there a different way to do this in the GL version.
